This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with analyzing facial videos to extract physiological signals. The use of deep spatio-temporal convolutional networks also suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on healthcare applications suggests that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
